<p>
  Now lets see some examples of these in play.
</p>
<p>
  Now that we have our arguments written using propositional forms
  we can verify that each of these arguments are valid using a 
  truth table, that is seeing they are all tautologies, or that 
  they are always true.
</p>
<p>
  We will do <em>Hypothetical Syllogism</em> and leave the rest as
  an exercise to the reader.
</p>
